tries press conference, Blair chooses Chuck over Dan, but Chuck rebuffs her when he is preoccupied with his father's return as head of Bass Industries who ousts Chuck to reclaim his former position as CEO. One week later; Lola hands over her inheritance share to Ivy, who in return promises to keep in touch and help her bring down their common enemy: Lily. Lola leaves town to go on tour with her acting troupe, while Ivy returns to Florida to plot her revenge against Lily. The disgraced Serena leaves town and reverts back to her old self by taking drugs and sleeping with her dealer, whilst the alienated Dan leaves for Rome and prepares to write another hurtful, tell-all book about the Upper East Side with the help of Georgina Sparks. Nate receives CCTV footage from Diana Payne of the real Gossip Girl (a hooded masked figure) stealing Serena's laptop on the night of Bart's return. Whilst in Paris, Blair goes to a casino where Chuck and Jack are scheming to bring down Bart Bass and tells Chuck it's now her turn to fight for him.\n----\n'''Title reference:''' The 2003 film ''[[The Lord of the Rings: The Return of the King]]''.\n|Aux4= 1.14<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2012/05/15/monday-final-ratings-how-i-met-your-mother-two-and-a-half-men-mike-molly-americas-got-talent-the-bachelorette-adjusted-up/134437/|title=Monday Final Ratings: 'How I Met Your Mother', 'Two and a Half Men', 'Mike & Molly', 'America's Got Talent' & 'The Bachelorette' Adjusted Up|last=Bibel|first=Sara|work=TV by the Numbers|date=May 15, 2012|accessdate=May 15, 2012}}</ref>\n |LineColor=FF5F5F\n}}\n}}</onlyinclude>\n\n==Production==\n[[The CW]] officially renewed the series for a fifth season on April 26, 2011.<ref>{{cite web |last=Ausiello |first=Michael |authorlink=Michael Ausiello |url=http://www.tvline.com/2011/04/breaking-cw-renews-vampire-diaries-supernatural-gossip-girl-and-90210/ |title=Breaking: CW Renews ''Vampire Diaries'', ''Supernatural'', ''Gossip Girl'' and ''90210'' |website=[[TVLine]] |date=April 26, 2011 |accessdate=May 21, 2011}}</ref>\n\nOn May 19, 2011, with the reveal of The CW's 2011\u201312 television schedule, ''Gossip Girl'' stayed on Monday night and moved to the 8:00 pm Eastern/7:00 pm Central timeslot as a lead-in to ''[[Hart of Dixie]]'', which is produced by ''Gossip Girl'''s executive producers [[Josh Schwartz]] and [[Stephanie Savage]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Mitovich |first=Matt Webb |url=http://www.tvline.com/2011/05/fall-tv-preview-cw-schedule/ |title=The CW's Fall Schedule: Sarah Michelle Gellar Back on Tuesdays, Nikita Makes Move |website=TVLine |date=May 19, 2011 |accessdate=May 21, 2011}}</ref> The fifth season premiered on Monday, September 26, 2011.<ref>{{cite web |last=Seidman |first=Robert |url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2011/06/20/the-cw-network-announces-fall-2011-premiere-dates/96084/ |title=The CW Network Announces Fall 2011 Premiere Dates |website=TV by the Numbers |date=June 20, 2011 |accessdate=June 20, 2011}}</ref>\n\nFilming for the season began on July 7, 2011.<ref>{{cite web |last=Bennett |first=Marcus |url=https://nymag.com/daily/entertainment/2011/06/penn_badgley_on_being_up_to_th.html |title=Penn Badgley Knows There's Skepticism About His Ability to Play Jeff Buckley |work=[[New York (magazine)|New York]] |date=June 29, 2011 |accessdate=June 26, 2011}}</ref> On August 3, 2011, The CW ordered two additional episodes for the fifth season, which will now total at 24.<ref>{{cite web |last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |url=https://www.deadline.com/2011/08/cw-orders-additional-episodes-of-four-returning-dramas/ |title=CW Orders Additional Episodes Of Four Returning Dramas |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=August 3, 2011 |accessdate=August 3, 2011}}</ref> Executive producer Joshua Safran announced that he would be \"pulling out all the stops\" to make the 100th episode of the show special, which is expected to air in January.<ref>{{cite web |last=Ausiello |first=Michael |authorlink=Michael Ausiello |url=http://www.tvline.com/2011/09/ask-ausiello-spoilers-on-glee-greys-anatomy-community/ |title=Ask Ausiello: Spoilers on ''Glee'', ''Grey's Anatomy'', ''Community'', ''Gossip Girl'', ''HIMYM'' and More! |website=TVLine |date=September 6, 2011 |accessdate=September 17, 2011}}</ref> On the date of the season premiere, the show used footage of the New York cityscape that showed the [[World Trade Center (1973\u20132001)|World Trade Center]] before the [[September 11 attacks]]. Footage containing the World Trade Center have been omitted by films and TV shows such as ''[[Sex and the City]]'' and ''[[The Sopranos]]'' to honor individuals who died in the attacks. The network has not responded to criticism regarding the usage of the footage.<ref>{{cite web |last=Eckstein |first=David |url=http://blog.zap2it.com/frominsidethebox/2011/09/gossip-girl-gaffe-world-trade-center-shown-in-season-premiere.html |title='Gossip Girl' gaffe: World Trade Center shown in season premiere |website=[[Zap2it]] |date=September 27, 2011 |accessdate=October 6, 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111007084113/http://blog.zap2it.com/frominsidethebox/2011/09/gossip-girl-gaffe-world-trade-center-shown-in-season-premiere.html |archive-date=October 7, 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nDespite dwindling ratings, series executives are confident the show will be renewed for a sixth season. Head of [[Warner Bros. Television]], [[Peter Roth (executive)|Peter Roth]] is also confident that the show will return, stating, \"I can't really say at this point, but I would hope and expect that there would be at least another year\u2014if not years\u2014to come.\"<ref name=\"100th episode spoilers\">{{cite web |last=Gonzalez |first=Sandra |url=http://insidetv.ew.com/2011/11/20/gossip-girl-scoop-100th-episode/ |title='Gossip Girl' scoop: Bosses planning on another season. Plus, the cast teases big moments in 100th episode |work=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |publisher=[[Time Inc.]] |date=November 20, 2011 |accessdate=November 21, 2011}}</ref> Later on, executive producer Stephanie Savage hinted that a sixth and final season is likely. \"We're not writing a series finale this year,\" said Savage. She added \"I checked in with the bosses to make sure we're not shooting ourselves in the foot\" and said the cast contracts run out at the end of the next season so \"that feels like probably an organic ending point\".<ref>{{cite web|last=Ryder|first=James|title=Gossip Girl to end after sixth season?|url=http://www.atvtoday.co.uk/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=3559:gossip-girl-to-end-after-sixth-season&catid=1:tv-media&Itemid=3|work=AVT Today|accessdate=January 27, 2012|date=January 26, 2012}}</ref>\n\n[[St. Vincent (musician)|St. Vincent]] performed \"Cruel\" and \"Cheerleader\" from her ''[[Strange Mercy]]'' album during the Valentine's Day episode.<ref>{{cite web|last=Pelly|first=Jenn|title=St. Vincent to Appear on \"Gossip Girl\"|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/45297-st-vincent-to-appear-on-gossip-girl/|website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|accessdate=February 2, 2012|date=February 1, 2012}}</ref>\n\n===Cast===\n{{Quote box |quote=Diana's entrance on the Upper East Side will change the lives of all our characters\u2014including and especially, Gossip Girl herself.|source=\u2014Stephanie Savage and Joshua Safran on Liz Hurley's introduction.<ref name=\"Elizabeth Hurley\"/>|align=right |width=30% |quoted=1 |salign=right}}\n\n[[Blake Lively]], [[Leighton Meester]], [[Penn Badgley]], [[Chace Crawford]], and [[Ed Westwick]] all returned as series regulars. [[Kaylee DeFer]] was upgraded to series regular status, while [[Taylor Momsen]] and [[Jessica Szohr]] exited the show, though they were both invited back as guest stars.<ref>{{cite web |last=Ausiello |first=Michael |authorlink=Michael Ausiello |url=http://www.tvline.com/2011/05/gossip-girl-taylor-momsen-jessica-szohr-leaving/ |title=''Gossip Girl'' Exclusive: Taylor Momsen and Jessica Szohr Not Returning For Season 5 |website=TVLine |date=May 9, 2011 |accessdate=May 21, 2011}}</ref> [[Kelly Rutherford]] and [[Matthew Settle]] also returned as regulars.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://blog.cwtv.com/2011/05/19/the-cw-announces-2011-2012-schedule/ |title=The CW Announces 2011\u20132012 Schedule |publisher=[[The CW]] |date=May 19, 2011 |accessdate=May 24, 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110529093919/http://blog.cwtv.com/2011/05/19/the-cw-announces-2011-2012-schedule/ |archivedate=May 29, 2011}}</ref>\n\nOn April 6, 2011, ''[[10 Things I Hate About You (TV series)|10 Things I Hate About You]]'' star [[Ethan Peck]] landed a guest-starring role on the show.<ref>{{cite web |last=Ausiello |first=Michael |authorlink=Michael Ausiello |url=http://www.tvline.com/2011/04/ask-ausiello-spoilers-smallville-glee-castle/ |title=Ask Ausiello: Spoilers on ''Smallville'', ''Glee'', ''Castle'', ''Bones'', ''How I Met Your Mother'' and More! |website=TVLine |date=April 5, 2011 |accessdate=May 23, 2011}}</ref> Peck made his debut in the fourth season finale and was in talks with producers for a recurring role for the fifth season.<ref>{{cite web |last=Wightman |first=Catriona |url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/ustv/s83/gossip-girl/news/a313091/ethan-peck-lands-gossip-girl-role.html |title=Ethan Peck 'lands Gossip Girl role' |website=[[Digital Spy]] |date=April 6, 2011 |accessdate=May 23, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Wengen |first=Deidre |url=http://www.phillyburbs.com/blogs/pop_culture_blog/gossip_girl/ethan-peck-to-appear-on-gossip-girl/article_3cf4f704-6059-11e0-89cf-001a4bcf6878.html |title=Ethan Peck to appear on Gossip Girl |website=phillyBurbs.com |date=April 6, 2011 |accessdate=May 23, 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110504085320/http://www.phillyburbs.com/blogs/pop_culture_blog/gossip_girl/ethan-peck-to-appear-on-gossip-girl/article_3cf4f704-6059-11e0-89cf-001a4bcf6878.html |archivedate=May 4, 2011}}</ref> Peck would later film his scenes with Lively for the season premiere. French actress and model [[Roxane Mesquida]] was cast as Beatrice, Louis' sister and Blair's nemesis in a recurring role for the fifth season.<ref>{{cite web |last=Ausiello |first=Michael |authorlink=Michael Ausiello |url=http://www.tvline.com/2011/06/gossip-girl-roxane-mesquida-blair-spoiler/ |title=''Gossip Girl'' Exclusive: Meet Blair's New Nemesis |website=TVLine |date=June 22, 2011 |accessdate=June 22, 2011}}</ref> Actress [[Elizabeth Hurley]] was cast as media mogul Diana Payne and starred in a multi-episode arc, with the character being described as \"a sexy, smart, self-made media mogul and an all-around force to be reckoned with.\"<ref name=\"Elizabeth Hurley\">{{cite web |last=Ausiello |first=Michael |authorlink=Michael Ausiello |url=http://www.tvline.com/2011/07/exclusive-gossip-girl-targets-elizabeth-hurley/ |title=Exclusive: ''Gossip Girl'' Targets Elizabeth Hurley |website=TVLine |date=July 5, 2011 |accessdate=July 5, 2011}}</ref> Former ''[[Lost (TV series)|Lost]]'' actor [[Marc Menard]] joined the cast in the role of Father Cavalia, a handsome priest from Monaco who will preside over Blair's wedding.<ref>{{cite web |last=Ausiello |first=Michael |authorlink=Michael Ausiello |url=http://www.tvline.com/2011/07/lost-hunk-joins-gossip-girl-marc-menard/ |title=Exclusive: ''Lost'' Hunk Joins Gossip Girl as... |website=TVLine |date=July 7, 2011 |accessdate=July 10, 2011}}</ref>\n\n[[Brian J. Smith]], known for his role on ''[[Stargate Universe]]'', had been cast as a love interest for Serena while she is in Los Angeles and would appearing on the show as Max, an aspiring chef.<ref>{{cite web |last=Ausiello |first=Michael |authorlink=Michael Ausiello |url=http://www.tvline.com/2011/07/brian-smith-serena-gossip-girl/ |title=''Gossip Girl'' Exclusive: Is ''Stargate: Universe'' Stud Serena's New Boyfriend? |website=TVLine |date=July 12, 2011 |accessdate=September 23, 2011}}</ref> [[Connor Paolo]], who went on to become a regular on [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]]'s ''[[Revenge (TV series)|Revenge]]'', did not return to the show as [[Eric van der Woodsen]] stating, \"I'm done. You should never go back in life. Only forward.\"<ref>{{cite web |last=Gelman |first=Vlada |url=http://www.tvline.com/2011/08/gossip-girl-connor-paolo-exit/ |title=Connor Paolo Confirms Gossip Exit: 'I'm Done' |website=TVLine |date=August 8, 2011 |accessdate=September 25, 2011}}</ref> In an interview with ''[[Elle (magazine)|Elle]]'' magazine on August 16, 2011, Momsen stated that she had quit the series to focus fully on her music career.<ref>{{cite web |last=Davis |first=Rebecca Willa |url=http://www.elle.com/culture/celebrities/news/a7091/taylor-momsens-quit-acting-forever-27238/ |title=Taylor Momsen's \"Quit Acting\" Forever |work=[[Elle (magazine)|Elle]] |date=August 16, 2011 |accessdate=February 11, 2018}}</ref> Hollywood stuntwoman [[Zo\u00eb Bell]] was slated to appear on the show and made her debut in the season premiere.<ref>{{cite web |last=Binkley |first=Christina |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB10001424052702303661904576456344161101326 |title=Fighting and Falling in High Heels |work=[[The Wall Street Journal]] |date=June 23, 2011 |accessdate=October 1, 2011}}</ref> ''[[New York (magazine)|New York]]'' magazine noted the appearance of American novelist [[Jay McInerney]], who reprised his role as writer Jeremiah Harris.<ref>{{cite web |last=Pressler |first=Jessica |url=https://nymag.com/daily/entertainment/2011/09/the_zip_codes_may_be_different.html |title=''Gossip Girl'' Recap: The Zip Codes May Be Different, But the Douchebags Are the Same |work=[[New York (magazine)|New York]] |date=September 27, 2011 |accessdate=October 1, 2011}}</ref> [[Aaron Tveit]], who previously portrayed Nate's cousin Tripp van der Bilt in the [[Gossip Girl (season 3)|third season]], returned to the show for a multi-episode arc.<ref>{{cite web |last=Mackenzie |first=Carina Adly |url=http://blog.zap2it.com/frominsidethebox/2011/10/gossip-girl-aaron-tveit-returns-for-multi-episode-arc-is-he-back-for-serena.html |title='Gossip Girl': Aaron Tveit returns for multi-episode arc... is he back for Serena? |website=Zap2it |date=October 4, 2011 |accessdate=October 6, 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111007052625/http://blog.zap2it.com/frominsidethebox/2011/10/gossip-girl-aaron-tveit-returns-for-multi-episode-arc-is-he-back-for-serena.html |archive-date=October 7, 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n[[Michelle Trachtenberg]] reprised her role as [[Georgina Sparks]], who was last seen in the fourth season finale. She made her first appearance during the show's 100th episode.<ref>{{cite web |last=Ausiello |first=Michael |authorlink=Michael Ausiello |url=http://www.tvline.com/2011/11/gossip-girl-michelle-trachtenberg-season-5/ |title=''Gossip Girl'' Exclusive: Michelle Trachtenberg Returning For [MAJOR SPOILER ALERT]! |website=TVLine |date=November 1, 2011 |accessdate=November 3, 2011}}</ref> Also returning was [[William Baldwin]] as Serena and Eric's father, [[List of Gossip Girl characters#William van der Woodsen|William van der Woodsen]], for the season's 17th episode, which aired in February 2012.<ref>{{cite web|last=dos Santos |first=Kristin |authorlink=Kristin dos Santos |url=http://www.eonline.com/news/watch_with_kristin/gossip_girl_scoop_billy_baldwin_set/284405 |title=''Gossip Girl'' Scoop: Billy Baldwin Set to Return for |website=[[E! Online]] |date=January 6, 2012 |accessdate=January 6, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120110013923/http://www.eonline.com/news/watch_with_kristin/gossip_girl_scoop_billy_baldwin_set/284405 |archivedate=January 10, 2012}}</ref> It was also reported that [[Desmond Harrington]], who made a cameo appearance in the fall finale, would return as Chuck's uncle, Jack Bass.<ref>{{cite web|last=Ausiello|first=Michael|title=Gossip Girl Exclusive: Look Who's Returning!|url=http://www.tvline.com/2012/01/gossip-girl-desmond-harrington-returns-season/|website=TVLine|accessdate=February 3, 2012|date=January 12, 2012}}</ref> Also guest starring was ''[[One Life to Live]]''{{'}}s alum David A. Gregory as a friend of the real Charlie Rhodes ([[Ella Rae Peck]]). Cobra Starship's [[Gabe Saporta]] made a cameo in season 5 finale.<ref>{{cite web|last=Marsters|first=Megan|title=TVLine Items: ''Boss'' Hires Jonathan Groff, ''Justified'' and ''Gossip Girl'' Casting News and More!|url=http://www.tvline.com/2012/02/tvline-items-jonathan-groff-boss-season-2-justified-gossip-girl/|website=TVLine|accessdate=February 6, 2012|date=February 6, 2012}}</ref>\n\n===Plot===\n{{Quote box |quote=I feel like if you're a fan of the show and you've been watching from the beginning, you're going to feel rewarded. But I also feel like if you're tuning in after a long time, I think you may feel like you've missed a lot, but we really try to hit on everything that's happened since [early on]. I'm very proud of it.|source=\u2014Joshua Safran on the series' 100th episode milestone.<ref name=\"100th episode spoilers\"/>|align=right |width=30% |quoted=1 |salign=right}}\n\nSeason five opens in Los Angeles, where a vacationing Chuck and Nate decide to visit Serena, who is working on a film set. Back in New York, Blair learns that planning a royal wedding can be stressful, especially with a baby on the way, and Dan discovers the consequences of writing candidly about his closest friends. Also, the surprise return of cousin Charlie will threaten to destroy the van der Woodsen family.<ref>{{cite web |last=Ausiello |first=Michael |authorlink=Michael Ausiello |url=http://www.tvline.com/2011/05/fall-preview-spoilers-on-next-seasons-gossip-girl-vampire-diaries-supernatural-and-more/ |title=Fall Preview: Spoilers on Next Season's ''Gossip Girl'', ''Vampire Diaries'', ''Supernatural'' and More! |website=TVLine |date=May 19, 2011 |accessdate=May 21, 2011}}</ref>\n\nConfused about Chuck's sudden change, Blair is determined to prove his behaviour is an act to win her back.\n\nThe series' 100th episode focused on Blair's wedding to prince Louis. \"I think it's our biggest episode since the pilot\", said executive producer Joshua Safran.<ref name=\"100th episode spoilers\"/>\n\n==Release==\nWith the move to 8:00pm, The CW charged $50,304 for a 30-second advertising slot before the fifth season began airing.<ref>{{cite web |last=Steinberg |first=Brian |url=http://adage.com/article/mediaworks/chart-american-idol-nfl-duke-priciest-tv-spot/230547/#mon |title='American Idol,' NFL Duke it out for Priciest TV Spot |work=[[Advertising Age]] |publisher=[[Crain Communications]] |date=October 24, 2011 |accessdate=October 24, 2011}}</ref>\n\n===Ratings===\nThe season premiere was watched by 1.37 million viewers and received a 0.7 rating in the Adults 19\u201349 demo,<ref name=\"GG season five premiere\"/> down 0.3 compared to last season's premiere.<ref>{{cite web |last=Calabria |first=Rosario T. |url=http://yourentertainmentnow.com/2010/09/21/broadcast-tv-ratings-for-monday-september-20-2010/ |title=Broadcast TV Ratings for Monday, September 20, 2010 |publisher=Your Entertainment Now |date=September 21, 2010 |accessdate=October 24, 2011}}</ref>\nEpisode 23 hit a new series low, hitting for the fourth time a total viewership below the one-million-viewer mark, to 869,000 viewers and a 0.4 in the 18-49 demographic.<ref>{{cite web |last=Hibberd |first=James |url=http://insidetv.ew.com/2012/05/08/gossip-girl-drops-to-all-time-low/ |title='Gossip Girl,' '2 Broke Girls' fall to ratings lows |work=Entertainment Weekly |date=May 8, 2012 |accessdate=May 8, 2012}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* List of [https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0397442/episodes?season=5 ''Gossip Girl'' season 5 episodes] on [[IMDb]]\n* {{Tv.com episodes|gossip-girl|68744|Gossip Girl|5}}\n\n{{Gossip Girl}}\n\n[[Category:2011 American television seasons]]\n[[Category:2012 American televisi