outube| publisher =| access-date =19 December 2019| quote = }}</ref>\n\n==Dominican Republic==\n* 6th Mountain Light Infantry Battalion (''6\u00ba Batall\u00f3n Cazadores de Monta\u00f1a'')<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ejercito.mil.do/2da-brigada-de-infanteria/cursos-2da-brigada#|title=CURSO DE EXPERTO EN OPERACIONES DE MONTA\u00d1AS \u201cCAZADOR\u201d.|website=ej\u00e9rcito.mil.do|accessdate=28 January 2019}}</ref>\n\n==El Salvador==\n* Mountain Commandos Company (''Compa\u00f1ia Comandos de Monta\u00f1a'')<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fuerzaarmada.mil.sv/?p=3903|title=DESTACAMENTO MILITAR N\u00daMERO CUATRO CLAUSUR\u00d3 EL CURSO DE \u201cCOMANDOS DE MONTA\u00d1A NO. 39\u201d EN MORAZAN|website=fuerzaarmada.mil.sv|accessdate=15 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.defensa.com/centro-america/las-elites-militares-salvador|title=Las \u00e9lites militares de El Salvador|website=defensa.com|accessdate=15 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n== France==\n[[File:7e BCA - Lyon-13-07-2016 (4).jpg|thumb|right|The 7e Bataillon de Chasseurs  Alpins on parade, 2016]]\n* [[27th Mountain Infantry Brigade (France)|27th Mountain Infantry Brigade]] (''27e\u00a0Brigade d'Infanterie de Montagne'')<ref name=\"27BIM\">{{cite web| url =https://www.defense.gouv.fr/terre/l-armee-de-terre/le-niveau-divisionnaire/1re-division/27e-brigade-d-infanterie-de-montagne| title =27e brigade d'infanterie de montagne\n | last =| first =| date = | website = Defense.gouv.fr| publisher =| access-date =31 January 2019| quote = }}</ref>\n** 27th Command and Signals Company (''27e Compagnie de Commandement et de Transmissions de Montagne'')<ref name=\"27BIM\"/>\n** 7th Alpine Light Infantry Battalion (''7e Bataillon de Chasseurs  Alpins'')<ref>{{cite web| url =https://www.defense.gouv.fr/terre/l-armee-de-terre/le-niveau-divisionnaire/1re-division/7e-bataillon-de-chasseurs-alpins| title =7e bataillon de chasseurs alpins | last =| first =| date = | website = Defense.gouv.fr| publisher =| access-date =