{"title_page": "Whatfor", "text_new": "{{More citations needed|date=January 2009}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name            = Whatfor\n| image           = \n| image_size      = \n| landscape       = <!-- yes, if wide image, otherwise leave blank -->\n| alt             = \n| caption         = \n| background      = group_or_band\n| alias           = \n| origin          = France\n| genre           = [[Pop music|Pop]]\n| years_active    = {{start date|2002}}\u2013{{end date|2003}}\n| label           = \n| associated_acts = \n| website         = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} -->\n| current_members = \n| past_members    = *Cyril\n*Erika\n*Nicolas\n*Monia\n}}\n'''Whatfor''' is the name of the band created by the second season of the popular French [[Reality television|reality-TV]] show ''[[Popstars (French TV series)|Popstars]]'' aired on [[RTL Group]] TV channel ''[[M6 (TV channel)|M6]]'' in fall 2002. The group consisted of Cyril and Erika (from [[Marseille]]), Nicolas (from [[Toulon]]) and Monia (from the [[Lyon]] suburbs).\n\nTheir first hit \"Plus haut\" (Higher) reached rank #1 in the French charts and so did their first and only album called ''Popstars''. Their musical style was a mix of modern [[dance music]], [[pop music|pop]] and [[R&B]], with a clear late 1970s [[disco]]/[[funk]] touch that is mainly because the mastermind behind this album, [[Philippe Saisse]], was the one behind the most successful albums of some great artists of that era like [[Chic (band)|Chic]] and [[Chaka Khan]].\n\nBut the success story ended as their second single called \"L'amour n'a pas de loi!\" (\"Love knows no law!\"), a cover of Swedish singer [[Carola H\u00e4ggkvist|Carola]]'s song \"A Kiss Goodbye\" (from her album ''My Show'') was a flop.\n\nThe group disbanded in 2003. Erika and Cyril founded a band together (Everton), and Nicolas tried a solo career, but none of their attempted were successful.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.chartsinfrance.net/actualite/news-76585.html|title=WhatFor : les premi\u00e8res images de leur reformation !|website=chartsinfrance.net|access-date=2017-10-09}}</ref> However, Nicolas went back to being a comedian which garnered him some fame.\n\n==Discography==\n\n===Album===\n* ''What For'' (2002)\n\n===Singles===\n* \"Plus haut\" (2002)\n* \"L'amour n'a pas de loi!\" (2003)\n\n{{Popstars (France)}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:French musical groups]]\n\n\n{{France-band-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{More citations needed|date=January 2009}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name            = Whatfor\n| image           = \n| image_size      = \n| landscape       = <!-- yes, if wide image, otherwise leave blank -->\n| alt             = \n| caption         = \n| background      = group_or_band\n| alias           = \n| origin          = France\n| genre           = [[Pop music|Pop]]\n| years_active    = {{start date|2002}}\u2013{{end date|2003}}\n| label           = \n| associated_acts = \n| website         = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} -->\n| current_members = \n| past_members    = *Cyril\n*Erika\n*Nicolas\n*Monia\n}}\n'''Whatfor''' is the name of the band created by the second season of the popular French [[Reality television|reality-TV]] show ''[[Popstars (French TV series)|Popstars]]'' aired on [[RTL Group]] TV channel ''[[M6 (TV channel)|M6]]'' in fall 2002. The group consisted of Cyril and Erika (from [[Marseille]]), Nicolas (from [[Toulon]]) and Monia (from the [[Lyon]] suburbs).\n\nTheir first hit \"Plus haut\" (Higher) reached rank #1 in the French charts and so did their first and only album called ''Popstars''. Their musical style was a mix of modern [[dance]] music, [[pop music|pop]] and [[R&B]], with a clear late 1970s [[disco]]/[[funk]] touch that is mainly because the mastermind behind this album, [[Philippe Saisse]], was the one behind the most successful albums of some great artists of that era like [[Chic (band)|Chic]] and [[Chaka Khan]].\n\nBut the success story ended as their second single called \"L'amour n'a pas de loi!\" (\"Love knows no law!\"), a cover of Swedish singer [[Carola H\u00e4ggkvist|Carola]]'s song \"A Kiss Goodbye\" (from her album ''My Show'') was a flop.\n\nThe group disbanded in 2003. Erika and Cyril founded a band together (Everton), and Nicolas tried a solo career, but none of their attempted were successful.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.chartsinfrance.net/actualite/news-76585.html|title=WhatFor : les premi\u00e8res images de leur reformation !|website=chartsinfrance.net|access-date=2017-10-09}}</ref> However, Nicolas went back to being a comedian which garnered him some fame.\n\n==Discography==\n\n===Album===\n* ''What For'' (2002)\n\n===Singles===\n* \"Plus haut\" (2002)\n* \"L'amour n'a pas de loi!\" (2003)\n\n{{Popstars (France)}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:French musical groups]]\n\n\n{{France-band-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Certes", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:Improve wikilinks, replaced:dancemusic \u2192dance music", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Whatfor"}
{"title_page": "WNRG-LP", "text_new": "{{See also|WNRG (disambiguation)}}\n{{Infobox radio station\n| name             = WNRG-LP\n| image            = \n| city             = [[Palm Bay, Florida]]\n| area             = \n| branding         = ''Energy 107.9''\n| slogan           = \"Brevard's Dance Connection\"\n| airdate          = April 5, [[2005 in radio|2005]]\n| last airdate     = March 2013\n| frequency        = 107.9 [[Megahertz|MHz]]\n| format           = Defunct\n| erp              = 100 [[watt]]s\n| haat             = 16.8 meters (55 feet)\n| class            = L1\n| facility_id      = 135652\n| coordinates      = {{coord|27|59|50|N|80|37|26|W}}\n| callsign_meaning = \n| former_callsigns = WGRV-LP (2004-2007)<br>WGRZ-LP (3/12/07-3/22/07)<br>WAET-LP (2007-2008)<ref name=\"fcc1\" />\n| affiliations     = \n| owner            = Public Radio Information Services of Central Florida, Inc.\n| licensee         = \n| sister_stations  = \n| webcast          = [http://wm4.spacialnet.com/WNRG Listen Live]\n| website          = \n}}\n\n'''WNRG-LP''' (107.9 [[FM broadcasting|FM]], \"Energy 107.9\") was a [[radio station]] [[city of license|licensed]] to serve [[Palm Bay, Florida]], United States.  The station was owned by Public Radio Information Services of Central Florida, Inc, and aired a [[dance music]] format, but since March 31, 2013, has been silent and its database deleted by the FCC.<ref name=\"arb1\">{{cite web|title=Station Information Profile |work=Arbitron |url=http://www.arbitron.com/ |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100301134627/http://www.arbitron.com/ |archivedate=March 1, 2010 }}</ref>\n\n==History==\n[[File:WGRV logo.png|200px|thumb|left|Logo as WGRV-LP]]\nThis station received its original [[construction permit]] from the [[Federal Communications Commission]] on June 4, [[2004 in radio|2004]].<ref name=\"fccp\">{{cite web |publisher=FCC Media Bureau |title=Application Search Details (BNPL-20010615AYN) |url=http://licensing.fcc.gov/cgi-bin/ws.exe/prod/cdbs/pubacc/prod/app_det.pl?Application_id=599772 |date=June 4, 2004}}</ref>  The new station was assigned the call letters '''WGRV-LP''' by the FCC on August 10, 2004.<ref name=\"fcc1\">{{cite web |title=Call Sign History |url=http://licensing.fcc.gov/cgi-bin/ws.exe/prod/cdbs/pubacc/prod/call_hist.pl?Facility_id=135652&Callsign=WNRG-LP |publisher=FCC Media Bureau CDBS Public Access Database}}</ref>  WGRV-LP has applied for its [[broadcast license|license to cover]] and that application was accepted by the FCC on November 18, 2005.<ref name=\"flic\">{{cite web |publisher=FCC Media Bureau |url=http://licensing.fcc.gov/cgi-bin/ws.exe/prod/cdbs/pubacc/prod/app_det.pl?Application_id=1073693 |title=Application Search Details (BLL-20051117ABK) |date=November 18, 2005}}</ref> The station was assigned the '''WNRG-LP''' [[call sign]] by the [[Federal Communications Commission]] on August 21, [[2008 in radio|2008]].<ref name=\"fcc1\"/>\n\nSince March 2013, WNRG-LP has been off the air and its studios and request phone lines were disconnected. The station's license was cancelled by the FCC on January 27, 2014.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{LPFM station data|WNRG}}\n*[http://www.fcc.gov/fcc-bin/FMTV-service-area?x=FL1048133.html WNRG-LP service area per the FCC database]\n\n{{Melbourne, Florida radio}}\n\n[[Category:Radio stations in Florida|NRG-LP]]\n[[Category:Low-power FM radio stations in Florida|NRG-LP]]\n[[Category:Radio stations established in 2005]]\n[[Category:Radio stations disestablished in 2013]]\n[[Category:Defunct radio stations in the United States]]\n[[Category:Palm Bay, Florida]]\n[[Category:2005 establishments in Florida]]\n[[Category:2013 disestablishments in Florida]]\n\n\n{{Florida-radio-station-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{See also|WNRG (disambiguation)}}\n{{Infobox radio station\n| name             = WNRG-LP\n| image            = \n| city             = [[Palm Bay, Florida]]\n| area             = \n| branding         = ''Energy 107.9''\n| slogan           = \"Brevard's Dance Connection\"\n| airdate          = April 5, [[2005 in radio|2005]]\n| last airdate     = March 2013\n| frequency        = 107.9 [[Megahertz|MHz]]\n| format           = Defunct\n| erp              = 100 [[watt]]s\n| haat             = 16.8 meters (55 feet)\n| class            = L1\n| facility_id      = 135652\n| coordinates      = {{coord|27|59|50|N|80|37|26|W}}\n| callsign_meaning = \n| former_callsigns = WGRV-LP (2004-2007)<br>WGRZ-LP (3/12/07-3/22/07)<br>WAET-LP (2007-2008)<ref name=\"fcc1\" />\n| affiliations     = \n| owner            = Public Radio Information Services of Central Florida, Inc.\n| licensee         = \n| sister_stations  = \n| webcast          = [http://wm4.spacialnet.com/WNRG Listen Live]\n| website          = \n}}\n\n'''WNRG-LP''' (107.9 [[FM broadcasting|FM]], \"Energy 107.9\") was a [[radio station]] [[city of license|licensed]] to serve [[Palm Bay, Florida]], United States.  The station was owned by Public Radio Information Services of Central Florida, Inc, and aired a [[dance]] music format, but since March 31, 2013, has been silent and its database deleted by the FCC.<ref name=\"arb1\">{{cite web|title=Station Information Profile |work=Arbitron |url=http://www.arbitron.com/ |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100301134627/http://www.arbitron.com/ |archivedate=March 1, 2010 }}</ref>\n\n==History==\n[[File:WGRV logo.png|200px|thumb|left|Logo as WGRV-LP]]\nThis station received its original [[construction permit]] from the [[Federal Communications Commission]] on June 4, [[2004 in radio|2004]].<ref name=\"fccp\">{{cite web |publisher=FCC Media Bureau |title=Application Search Details (BNPL-20010615AYN) |url=http://licensing.fcc.gov/cgi-bin/ws.exe/prod/cdbs/pubacc/prod/app_det.pl?Application_id=599772 |date=June 4, 2004}}</ref>  The new station was assigned the call letters '''WGRV-LP''' by the FCC on August 10, 2004.<ref name=\"fcc1\">{{cite web |title=Call Sign History |url=http://licensing.fcc.gov/cgi-bin/ws.exe/prod/cdbs/pubacc/prod/call_hist.pl?Facility_id=135652&Callsign=WNRG-LP |publisher=FCC Media Bureau CDBS Public Access Database}}</ref>  WGRV-LP has applied for its [[broadcast license|license to cover]] and that application was accepted by the FCC on November 18, 2005.<ref name=\"flic\">{{cite web |publisher=FCC Media Bureau |url=http://licensing.fcc.gov/cgi-bin/ws.exe/prod/cdbs/pubacc/prod/app_det.pl?Application_id=1073693 |title=Application Search Details (BLL-20051117ABK) |date=November 18, 2005}}</ref> The station was assigned the '''WNRG-LP''' [[call sign]] by the [[Federal Communications Commission]] on August 21, [[2008 in radio|2008]].<ref name=\"fcc1\"/>\n\nSince March 2013, WNRG-LP has been off the air and its studios and request phone lines were disconnected. The station's license was cancelled by the FCC on January 27, 2014.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{LPFM station data|WNRG}}\n*[http://www.fcc.gov/fcc-bin/FMTV-service-area?x=FL1048133.html WNRG-LP service area per the FCC database]\n\n{{Melbourne, Florida radio}}\n\n[[Category:Radio stations in Florida|NRG-LP]]\n[[Category:Low-power FM radio stations in Florida|NRG-LP]]\n[[Category:Radio stations established in 2005]]\n[[Category:Radio stations disestablished in 2013]]\n[[Category:Defunct radio stations in the United States]]\n[[Category:Palm Bay, Florida]]\n[[Category:2005 establishments in Florida]]\n[[Category:2013 disestablishments in Florida]]\n\n\n{{Florida-radio-station-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Certes", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:Improve wikilinks, replaced:dancemusic \u2192dance music", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/WNRG-LP"}
